  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And when they had eaten enough,.... Were satisfied, having eaten a full meal: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "they lightened the ship; of its burden, that it might the better carry them to the shore, and that by the following method: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and cast out the wheat into the sea; which seems to have been part of the ship's provision; or one part of their lading, which they brought from Egypt, and were carrying to Italy: they had cast out some of the goods of the ship before, and also the tackling of the ship, and now, last of all, the wheat; for what was eatable they reserved till last, not knowing to what extremity they might be reduced. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and cast out the wheat into the sea; which seems to have been part of the ship's provision; or one part of their lading, which they brought from Egypt, and were carrying to Italy: they had cast out some of the goods of the ship before, and also the tackling of the ship, and now, last of all, the wheat; for what was eatable they reserved till last, not knowing to what extremity they might be reduced. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
